The paper proposes a model that combines restricted Boltzmann machines with feed-forward neural networks for latent truth discovery, which is a problem related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with natural language processing and information retrieval, which are covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively. Finally, the paper involves data management and probabilistic modeling, which are relevant to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), respectively.
